Life’s not fair. Not by a long shot. Just look at all the rain of the last week or so. Yes, we do need the rain, and yes, it is an answer to many prayers following a devastating drought which ravaged large parts of the country. But come on. When the American duo The Weather Girls sang about rain, it was because it was raining men. Who will ever forget their 1983 hit in which they shared the good news: “Tonight, for the first time, just about half-past ten, for the first time in history, it’s gonna start raining men.”...